<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
The specific epithet is an adjective formed from the Greek terms 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">ozotos</emphasis>
, meaning branching, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">litos</emphasis>
, meaning simple, and is used to describe the distinctly simple pygidial plates of this species.
</paragraph>
